# Signet: testing workflow (required)

## After any non-trivial change

- Run the fast suite: `npm test`
- If the change touches server routing/DB/auth/session logic: also run `npm test` (includes API integration tests)
- If the change touches the editor UI (`public/`), selection/cursor math, undo/redo, clipboard, or chapter rendering: also run `npm run test:e2e`
- Before finishing a task (or when unsure): run the full suite: `npm run test:all`

## Fix-forward policy

- If any test fails, **fix the root cause** (don’t weaken assertions unless the behavior is intentionally changing).
- If an E2E test is flaky, stabilize it by:
  - waiting on concrete UI signals (`toBeVisible`, `toHaveText`, `expect.poll` on DOM state)
  - avoiding timing-based sleeps
  - preferring stable selectors (`#id` and existing classnames in `public/app.html`)

## Test architecture notes (project-specific)

- Unit + API integration tests use Node’s built-in runner (`node --test`) under `test/`.
- Browser regression tests use Playwright under `e2e/` (Chromium-first).
- E2E artifacts are written to the OS temp directory (not the repo) to avoid OneDrive/Windows permission issues.
